{
  "texts": [
    "Formally, we define the cross-attention from queries located at X to keys and values located at Ξ as:",
    "where Q = q(X), K = k(Ξ), and V = v(Ξ) are the query, key, and value embeddings defined over X and Ξ, respectively; d k is the key/query dimensionality; and m is a scaling factor, either fixed or learned as in ALiBi (Press et al., 2022).",
    "Intuitively, the bias B imposes stronger penalties for distant pairs (x i, ξ j), reducing their attention weights and encouraging the model to focus on local interactions during interpolation.",
    "For the architecture of the CNN, we adopt a design similar to that of Yu et al. (2023).",
    "In our case, it takes as input the output of the interpolation module, u 0:L-1 (Ξ), and lifts it to a higherdimensional representation of size h comp using a causal convolution layer (see fig. 3)."
  ]
}